title: Family at War Series 3
description:
How the events of WW 2 affected various members of a lower middle class family in Liverpool, the emphasis being on life on the home front. Created by John Finch and ran from 1970-1972. Please remember that although DVD quality, the series is old!! Please seed. 
Series 3 includes 20 episodes:
The Lucky Ones
For the Duration
Happy Returns
The Things You Never Told Me
You Can Choose Your Friends
Flesh and Blood
Spread a Little Happiness
Take It on Trust
This Year, Next Year
The Fundamental Things Apply
Thicker Than Water
Breaking Point
The Lost Ones
The Sensible Thing
Under New Management
Coming Home
A Faint Refrain
Two Fathers
The Old Order Changeth
Yielding Place to New
